column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] 13: Babel. Witt Library. Herri met de Bles, Sale Groupe, Berlin, 27-29 May, 1935, N° 2. The tower is square, but in the foreground appears the ruler (oriental) with his suite and a man the builder kneeling before him (repr. [Helmut] Minkowski, Bild 193 [= Aus dem Nebel der Vergangenheit steigt der Turm zu Babel: Bilder aus 1000 Jahren, Berlin: Rembrandt, 1960] ). Square is the older form of the Tower: Bruegel round like Harbour of Naples.</content>
<part_of.title>Towers of Babel. Reproductions. Towers of Babel by other Artists.</part_of.title>
